The Chairman of All Progressives Congress (APC) in Osun State, Gboyega Famodun, has urged the Seventh Osun State House of Assembly to brace up through positive engagement with the Executive and other stakeholders to lift the development portfolio of the state as the assembly is being inaugurated today.He challenged the legislators “to continue the positive engagement with the Executive in the best interest of good governance.” Also, the party, in a statement by its Publicity Director, Kunle Oyatomi, urged the lawmakers to “brace up for hardwork because the challenges ahead will stretch their abilities to the limits.”He said the party would offer whatever assistance it could give for them to excel in their performance. To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .